  "suspected_trap": "The -e 2 finalize is the trap: it emits exactly ONE CONFIG_CHANGE record at load (~184 B, f3 3.2), then is volume-neutral. A naive impl that sees -e 2 as 'a rule' and assigns it a syscall-class rate band would invent ongoing volume that does not exist. It must be tiered NEGATIVE/zero, like -D/-b/-f (f3 2.1)."
